                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/116.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>354. Department’s 287, July 20. Have brought Ghiloni case personally again to
                    attention Minister Foreign Affairs who promises to have matter studied promptly.
                    He seems more favorable than formerly to idea of naturalization.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
